		/// reason for this is that a pointer to the context is stored in the `ma_device` structure.<br/>
		/// Example 1 - Default Initialization<br/>
		/// ----------------------------------<br/>
		/// The example below shows how to initialize the context using the default configuration.<br/>
		/// ```c<br/>
		/// ma_context context;<br/>
		/// ma_result result = ma_context_init(NULL, 0, NULL, <br/>
		/// &context<br/>
		/// );<br/>
